          <div class="project-details">
            <div class="vertical-center">
              <h3>Bring Home<br/> To Mom</h3>
              <hr class="flared-edges"><br/>
              <p><em>Overview:</em> Bring Home To Mom is a match-making and date-planning app targeted to parents.  Parents create profiles for their children, browse and filter for potential matches, plan dates while communicating with the other child's parents, and split the cost of the upcoming date so everything is prepaid.</p>
              <p><em>Technology:</em> Ruby on Rails and PostgreSQL back end.  JavaScript, jQuery, AJAX, and handlebars.js on front end to deliver single-page user experience across much of the site.  API integrations with Stripe for payments, Twilio for MMS notifications, Cloudinary for images, and Rotten Tomatoes and OMDB for local movie listings.</p>
              <p><em>Background:</em> Final project at Dev Bootcamp.  I conceived and pitched the idea, and led a team of four to create the product in exactly one week. </p>
              <p><em>Creators:</em> Jonathan Berk, Sophie Garden, Tony Mai, Kevin Ceballos.</p>
              <nav class="project-links">
                <a class="video" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IlpoisuHNxc" target="_blank">Video</a>
                <a href="https://github.com/berkjon/bring-home-to-mom" target="_blank">GitHub</a>
                <a href="http://bringhometomom.herokuapp.com/" target="_blank">Live</a>
              </nav>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>


        <!-- 98PROBLEMS  -->
        <div class="project-content" id="ninety8problems">
          <div class="mobile-project-header">
            <h3>#98problems</h3>
            <hr class="flared-edges"><br/>
