          <div class="project-details">
            <div class="vertical-center">
              <h3>Shelfworm</h3>
              <hr class="flared-edges"><br/>
              <p><em>Overview:</em> Shelfworm is a virtual bookshelf.  Users sign in with their Goodreads account, and Shelfworm automatically creates a neatly stylized page of all books that user has read, sorted by rating.  Cover art is imported automatically, and on mouse hover, the cover rotates to reveal detailed information including the user's rating and review.</p>
              <p><em>Technology:</em> Ruby, Sinatra and PostgreSQL back end.  JavaScript, jQuery & AJAX to deliver 'infinite scroll' functionality for large bookshelves.  Hover effects with CSS.  Redis and Resque for background jobs.  API and OAuth 1.0 integration with Goodreads.  Cover images sourced from Goodreads, Open Library and LibraryThing.</p>
              <p><em>Background:</em> Solo project completed in one week at Dev Bootcamp.</p>
